\subsection{Working Principle}

The Arduino firmware automatically generates all eight possible binary
combinations of inputs $A$, $B$, and $C$ in a continuous loop. The LEDs
connected to pins \texttt{D2}, \texttt{D3}, and \texttt{D4} provide a visual
indication of the current input state. The LED connected to pin \texttt{D5}
represents the output $Y$. Since the simplified Boolean expression evaluates to
$Y = 1$ unconditionally, the output LED remains \textbf{continuously illuminated}
for every input combination, providing clear empirical confirmation of the
simplification.

